    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <head>Municipal Council of Hamilton, Canada West</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayor’s Office, <placeName>Hamilton, C.
                                    W.</placeName>
                        </hi>
                    </placeName>, <lb/>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-26">
                        <hi rend="italic">April 26, A.
                                D. 1865</hi>
                    </date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor, by direction of the
                        municipal corporation of the city of Hamilton, Canada West, to enclose a
                        copy of resolutions passed by that body on hearing the sad news of the
                        assassination of the late President, Abraham Lincoln, and to respectfully
                        request that you will be pleased to lay the same before the President.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES MAGILL,</signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mayor of Hamilton, C. W</hi>.</closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps"> William H. Seward</hi>, <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
